# Fullstack Monorepo Standards

## Architecture

- Follow layered architecture on backend: routes -> controllers -> services -> models.
- Keep routes focused on routing, validation, and middleware wiring only.
- Never place business logic in routes.
- Keep controllers thin: parse request input, call services, and shape HTTP responses.
- Keep business rules in services; keep data access concerns in models.

## Implementation Practices

- Use async/await consistently for asynchronous flows.
- Use TypeScript types everywhere on the backend (request contracts, service inputs/outputs, and model-level interfaces/types).
- Prefer simple, readable solutions over complex abstractions.
- Do not introduce new libraries unless they are clearly necessary and justified.

## Frontend State

- Keep frontend state local by default.
- Only lift state or introduce shared/global state when explicitly required by the feature.
